data.name: Rowlet
data.flavorText: This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.

data.name: Litten
data.flavorText: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.

data.name: Popplio
data.flavorText: This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It's famous for being a hard worker.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.

data.name: Rockruff
data.flavorText: It's considered to be a good Pokémon for beginners because of its friendliness, but its disposition grows rougher as it grows up.

data.name: Pikipek
data.flavorText: It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to drill holes in trees. It uses holes for food storage and for nesting.

data.name: Litten
data.flavorText: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.

data.name: Togedemaru
data.flavorText: The long hairs on its back act as lightning rods. The bolts of lightning it attracts are stored as energy in its electric sac.

data.name: Shiinotic
data.flavorText: It emits flickering spores that cause drowsiness. When its prey succumb to sleep, this Pokémon feeds on them by sucking in their energy.

data.name: Bruxish
data.flavorText: It stuns its prey with psychokinesis and then grinds them to mush with its strong teeth. Even Shellder's shell is no match for it.

data.name: Passimian
data.flavorText: They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable—they will never let down a comrade.

data.name: Oranguru
data.flavorText: Deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy, this Pokémon abides. On rare occasions, it shows up at the beach to match wits with Slowking.

data.name: Zygarde
data.flavorText: This is Zygarde's form at times when it uses its overwhelming power to suppress those who endanger the ecosystem.

data.name: Alolan Sandslash
data.flavorText: Fleeing a volcanic eruption, it settled on a snowy mountain. As it races through the snowfields, it sends up a spray of snow.

data.name: Oricorio
data.flavorText: This Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. Its elegant, attractive dance will send the minds and hearts of its enemies to another world.

data.name: Mudsdale
data.flavorText: It spits a mud that provides resistance to both wind and rain, so the walls of old houses were often coated with it.

data.name: Drampa
data.flavorText: It has a compassionate personality, but if it is angered, it completely destroys its surroundings with its intense breath.

data.name: Rowlet

data.name: Litten
data.flavorText: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.

data.name: Popplio
data.flavorText: This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It's famous for being a hard worker.

data.name: Lurantis
data.flavorText: It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantis's vivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy this work and treat it as their hobby.

data.name: Tsareena
data.flavorText: Its long, striking legs aren't just for show but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.

data.name: Turtonator
data.flavorText: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently if struck. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.

data.name: Vikavolt
data.flavorText: It produces electricity via an electrical organ in its abdomen. It overwhelms bird Pokémon with shocking beams of electrical energy.

data.name: Mimikyu
data.flavorText: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.

data.name: Tapu Koko
data.flavorText: This guardian deity of Melemele is brimming with curiosity. It summons thunderclouds and stores their lightning inside its body.

data.flavorText: This guardian deity of Melemele is brimming with curiosity. It summons thunderclouds and stores their lightning inside its body.

data.name: Jangmo-o
data.flavorText: It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.

data.name: Komala
data.flavorText: It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.

data.name: Cosmog
data.flavorText: Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowly grows as it collects dust from the atmosphere.

data.name: Alolan Meowth
data.flavorText: This Pokémon was not originally found in Alola. Human actions caused a surge in their numbers, and they went feral. They're prideful and crafty.

data.name: Togedemaru
data.flavorText: The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this Pokémon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.

data.name: Tapu Lele
data.flavorText: This guardian deity of Akala is guilelessly cruel. The fragrant aroma of flowers is the source of its energy.

data.name: Seviper
data.flavorText: In battle, it uses its bladed tail to counter any Zangoose. It secretes a deadly venom in its tail.

data.name: Crabominable
data.flavorText: It aimed for the top but got lost and ended up on a snowy mountain. Being forced to endure the cold, this Pokémon evolved and grew fur.

data.name: Zygarde
data.flavorText: This is Zygarde's form at times when it uses its overwhelming power to suppress those who endanger the ecosystem.

data.name: Bewear
data.flavorText: This immensely dangerous Pokémon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.

data.name: Alolan Meowth
data.flavorText: This Pokémon was not originally found in Alola. Human actions caused a surge in their numbers, and they went feral. They're prideful and crafty.

data.name: Golisopod
data.flavorText: With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawater—or even air—right in two.

data.name: Dhelmise
data.flavorText: Swinging its massive anchor, it can KO Wailord in a single blow. What appears to be green seaweed is actually its body.

data.name: Lucario
data.flavorText: Not only does it perceive auras, but it has also gained the power to control them. It employs them in battle.

data.name: Decidueye
data.flavorText: It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision they can pierce a pebble at distances over a hundred yards.

data.name: Tapu Bulu
data.flavorText: It pulls large trees up by the roots and swings them around. It causes vegetation to grow, and then it absorbs energy from the growth.

data.name: Silvally
data.flavorText: Although its name was Type: Null at first, the boy who evolved it into this form gave it the name by which it is now known.

data.name: Alolan Raichu
data.flavorText: It only evolves to this form in the Alola region. According to researchers, its diet is one of the causes of this change.

data.name: Shining Ho-Oh
data.flavorText: A legend says that its body glows in seven colors. A rainbow is said to form behind it when it flies.

data.name: Alolan Raichu
data.flavorText: It only evolves to this form in the Alola region. According to researchers, its diet is one of the causes of this change.

data.name: Salazzle
data.flavorText: For some reason, only females have been found. It creates a reverse harem of male Salandit that it lives with.

data.name: Regirock
data.flavorText: Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, it attaches rocks to repair itself.

data.name: Registeel
data.flavorText: Tempered by pressure underground over tens of thousands of years, its body cannot be scratched.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.

data.name: Mewtwo
data.flavorText: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

data.name: Shining Celebi
data.flavorText: This Pokémon wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.

data.name: Shining Lugia
data.flavorText: It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.

data.name: Zorua
data.flavorText: It changes so it looks like its foe, tricks it, and then uses that opportunity to flee.

data.name: Marshadow
data.flavorText: Able to conceal itself in shadows, it never appears before humans, so its very existence was the stuff of myth.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.

data.name: Latias
data.flavorText: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.

data.name: Latios
data.flavorText: A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.

data.name: Zoroark
data.flavorText: Each has the ability to fool a large group of people simultaneously. They protect their lair with illusory scenery.

data.name: Tapu Fini
data.flavorText: The dense fog it creates brings the downfall and destruction of its confused enemies. Ocean currents are the source of its energy.

data.name: Marshadow
data.flavorText: Able to conceal itself in shadows, it never appears before humans, so its very existence was the stuff of myth.

data.name: Wash Rotom
data.flavorText: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

data.name: Lucario
data.flavorText: They can detect the species of a living being—and its emotions—from over half a mile away. They control auras and hunt their prey in packs.

data.name: Heatran
data.flavorText: Boiling blood, like plasma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.

data.name: Gumshoos
data.flavorText: It adores having Rattata and Raticate for dinner, but as it's diurnal, it never encounters them. This Pokémon boasts incredible patience.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.

data.name: Mimikyu
data.flavorText: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by horror and died of the shock.

data.name: Lycanroc
data.flavorText: Bathed in the setting sun of evening, Lycanroc has undergone a special kind of evolution. An intense fighting spirit underlies its calmness.

data.name: Dawn Wings Necrozma
data.flavorText: Lunala no longer has a will of its own. Now under the control of Necrozma, it continuously expels all of its energy.

data.name: Dusk Mane Necrozma
data.flavorText: This is its form with it is devouring the light of Solgaleo. It pounces on its foes and then slashes them with the claws on its four limbs and back.

data.name: Ash's Pikachu
data.flavorText: This Pikachu is wearing its Trainer's cap. Since the cap's not the right size, the fit is a bit loose.

data.name: Ash's Pikachu
data.flavorText: This form of Pikachu is somewhat rare. It wears the hat of its Trainer, who is also its partner.

data.name: Pheromosa
data.flavorText: One of the Ultra Beasts. It refuses to touch anything, perhaps because it senses some uncleanness in this world.

data.name: Xurkitree
data.flavorText: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. It raided a power plant, so people think it energizes itself with electricity.

data.name: Malamar
data.flavorText: It lures prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.

data.name: Lycanroc
data.flavorText: Bathed in the setting sun of evening, Lycanroc has undergone a special kind of evolution. An intense fighting spirit underlies its calmness.

data.name: Exeggcute
data.flavorText: Its six eggs use telepathy to communicate among themselves. It is believed to carry plant genes and the genes of other species.

data.name: Rockruff
data.flavorText: As they develop, their disposition grows more violent and aggressive. Many Trainers find them too much to handle and abandon them.

data.flavorText: Lunala no longer has a will of its own. Now under the control of Necrozma, it continuously expels all of its energy.

data.name: Dusk Mane Necrozma
data.flavorText: This is its form with it is devouring the light of Solgaleo. It pounces on its foes and then slashes them with the claws on its four limbs and back.

data.name: Alolan Sandslash
data.flavorText: This Pokémon's steel spikes are sheathed in ice. Stabs from these spikes cause deep wounds and severe frostbite as well.

data.name: Alolan Ninetales
data.flavorText: Possessing a calm demeanor, this Pokémon was revered as a deity incarnate before it was identified as a regional variant of Ninetales.

data.name: Kyogre
data.flavorText: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.

data.name: Manectric
data.flavorText: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.

data.name: Celesteela
data.flavorText: One kind of Ultra Beast. Witnesses have seen it burn down a forest by expelling gas from its two arms.

data.name: Delcatty
data.flavorText: It is highly popular among female Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.

data.name: Latias
data.flavorText: It can telepathically communicate with people. It changes its appearance using its down that refracts light.

data.name: Latios
data.flavorText: It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokémon that dislikes fighting.

data.name: Salamence
data.flavorText: It flies around on its wings, which have grown in at last. In its happiness, it gushes hot flames, burning up the fields it passes over.

data.name: Kyurem
data.flavorText: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

data.name: Moltres
data.flavorText: It is said to be the legendary bird Pokémon of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flare of flames.

data.name: Articuno
data.flavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

data.name: Zapdos
data.flavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.

data.name: Suicune
data.flavorText: Said to be the embodiment of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.

data.name: Raikou
data.flavorText: This rough Pokémon stores energy inside its body, then sweeps across the land, shooting off electricity.

data.name: Giratina
data.flavorText: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.

data.name: Tapu Lele
data.flavorText: As it flutters about, it scatters its strangely glowing scales. Touching them is said to restore good health on the spot.

data.name: Rowlet
data.flavorText: This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.

data.name: Salandit
data.flavorText: It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous gas. When its enemies become disoriented from inhaling the gas, it attacks them.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: It's in its nature to store electricity. It feel stressed now and then if it's unable to fully discharge the electricity.

data.name: Charizard
data.flavorText: When expelling a blast of superhot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns more intensely.

data.name: Zapdos
data.flavorText: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

data.name: Nidoqueen
data.flavorText: It uses its scaly, rugged body to seal the entrance of its nest and protect its young from predators.

data.name: Jirachi
data.flavorText: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: It's in its nature to store electricity. It feels stressed now and then if it's unable to fully discharge the electricity.

data.name: Mimikyu
data.flavorText: A lonely Pokémon, it conceals its terrifying appearance beneath an old rag so it can get closer to people and other Pokémon.

data.name: Deoxys
data.flavorText: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokémon. It appears where auroras are seen.

data.name: Ultra Necrozma
data.flavorText: This is its form when it has absorbed overwhelming light energy. It fires laser beams from all over its body.

data.name: Detective Pikachu
data.flavorText: He loves to show off his vast knowledge. This expressive Pikachu is like a middle-aged man.

data.name: Meltan
data.flavorText: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

data.name: Volcanion
data.flavorText: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It's said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.

data.name: Stakataka
data.flavorText: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

data.name: Melmetal
data.flavorText: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.

data.name: Persian
data.flavorText: Although the jewel on its forehead appears to be a different color than those of Alolan Persian, it's mostly made of the same material.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: It's in its nature to store electricity. It feels stressed now and then if it's unable to fully discharge the electricity.

data.name: Eevee
data.flavorText: Current studies show it can evolve into an incredible eight different species of Pokémon.

data.name: Typhlosion
data.flavorText: It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur together to cause huge explosions.

data.name: Flareon
data.flavorText: If it inhales deeply, that's a sign it's about to attack. Prepare to be hit by flames of over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit!

data.name: Detective Pikachu
data.flavorText: He was the partner of Tim's father, Harry, who has gone missing. This Pikachu loves the dark coffee at the Hi-Hat Cafe.

data.name: Detective Pikachu
data.flavorText: Skilled in deduction, he's a self-proclaimed "great detective." His detective hat is his trademark.

data.name: Bulbasaur
data.flavorText: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this Pokémon.

data.name: Psyduck
data.flavorText: Using psychokinesis gives it a headache, so it normally passes the time spacing out and doing as little as possible.

data.name: Snubbull
data.flavorText: It grows close to others easily and is also easily spoiled. The disparity between its face and its actions makes many young people wild about it.

data.name: Amoonguss
data.flavorText: They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.

data.name: Tapu Fini
data.flavorText: This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.

data.name: Necrozma
data.flavorText: It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It's apparently from another world.

data.name: Terrakion
data.flavorText: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.

data.name: Sudowoodo
data.flavorText: It's so popular with the elderly that there's a magazine devoted to this Pokémon. Fans obsess over the particular length and angle of its arms.

data.name: Vikavolt
data.flavorText: It has an organ that generates electricity in its abdomen. It concentrates energy in its strong jaws and fires off powerful jolts of electricity.

data.name: Stakataka
data.flavorText: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

data.name: Mewtwo
data.flavorText: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA-engineering experiments.

data.name: Mew
data.flavorText: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.

data.name: Buzzwole
data.flavorText: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

data.name: Entei
data.flavorText: A Pokémon that races across the land. It is said that one is born every time a new volcano appears.

data.name: Phione
data.flavorText: When the water warms, they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.

data.name: Blacephalon
data.flavorText: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It's apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

data.name: Mismagius
data.flavorText: Feared for its wrath and the curses it spreads, this Pokémon will also, on a whim, cast spells that help people.

data.name: Terrakion
data.flavorText: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.

data.name: Celebi
data.flavorText: This Pokémon wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.

data.name: Victini
data.flavorText: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

data.name: Charizard
data.flavorText: This Pokémon was created by Mewtwo to prove that copies can be even more powerful than their originals.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.

data.name: Armored Mewtwo
data.flavorText: Mewtwo was on a rampage searching for meaning to its existence in this world when Giovanni suppressed and controlled its power.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: It's in its nature to store electricity. It feels stressed now and then if it's unable to fully discharge the electricity.

data.name: Eevee
data.flavorText: The question of why only Eevee has such unstable genes has still not been solved.

data.name: Leafeon
data.flavorText: Although it doesn't like disputes, it will sharpen the leaf on its tail into a blade and fight if it has to protect its friends.

data.name: Glaceon
data.flavorText: It protects itself by freezing its fur into sharp needles. It can drop its body temperature below –75 degrees Fahrenheit.

data.name: Regigigas
data.flavorText: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.

data.name: Aipom
data.flavorText: As it did more and more with its tail, its hands became clumsy. It makes its nest high in the treetops.

data.name: Mismagius
data.flavorText: Feared for its wrath and the curses it spreads, this Pokémon will also, on a whim, cast spells that help people.
